    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Fixed bridges that extend without hinges or joints across three or more supports, making them capable of resisting bending and shearing forces at all sections throughout their length; continuous bridges are firmly supported in the perpendicular direction by piers and abutments. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
